ğŸ§µ(6/6)

When I heard that @roboshima and @BenTopkins were building a team to make games in web3 I knew I wanted to get involved.

They have a track record of making building great games!

ğŸ§µ(5/6)

But games in web3 should still be about a fun gaming experience at its core.

No better way to make great games than by having world-class game devs entering the ecosystem.

ğŸ§µ(4/6)

There is a beautiful feeling of camaraderie within web3 gaming communities that I haven't seen anywhere else.

Everyone supports each other at every corner, anything from onboarding to building, it's a by-product of owning your own game assets.

ğŸ§µ(3/6)

Ever since learning about NFT Gaming last year I knew I had to get involved, @AxieInfinity stood out from the rest for a very particulate reason - Community!

ğŸ§µ(2/6)

Like many of us, gaming has always been a huge part of my life, playing thousands of hours across many titles and genres.

Going from web2 to web3 gaming has been no different.

ğŸ§µ(1/6)

I'm very honoured to announce that I've joined the @PlaySkateX team as their community manager!

Excited to build fun games in web3! ğŸ›¹

I could expand a lot more but I hope you can see how both sides of the coin can be a good thing for the space overall.

Would love to hear everyones opinion on the matter but a lot of the arguments over the past day have not been productive. Build MORE, hate LESS!

ğŸ§µ(4/4)

If you don't think other P2E games are competition then this is also a good thing!

Developers can learn from each other and their mistakes, being able to make faster progress and innovating in sectors where it would normally take longer to advance in.

ğŸ§µ(3/4)

Believe it or not competition is a GOOD thing for the space.

Developers will have to constantly improve their product with new updates, features and deliver on a timely manner to stay competitive!

ğŸ§µ(2/4)

Let's start with a poll - do you think other P2E games are competition for @AxieInfinity?

I see both answers as a net positive, here are my 2 cents on the matter â¬‡ï¸
